  "description": [
    "VADM Beakley Named District Commandant ADM Wallace M Beaklev Depute Commander in Chief U S Atlantic Fleet Norfolk Va will assume duties as Com mandant of the First Naval District about 1 Sept ISXS3 ADM Beaklev will relieve RADM Arthur 11 Tavlor New port Naval Base Commander as Commandant of the First Naval District RADM Tax lor assumed duties as Commandant on 16 April 1963 when the former Commandant RADM Joseph H Wellings suffered a stroke The new Commandant was the Commander of the U S Seventh Fleet from January 1957 until November 1958 He then became Deputy Chief of Naval Opera tions for Fleet Operations and Readiness In September 1961 he assumed duties as Deputy Com mander in Chief and Chief of Staff and Aide to the Commander in Chief I S Atlantic Fleet Decorations VADM Beaklev holds two of of the Navys highest awards the Navy Cross and the Legion of Merit He was awarded the Navy Cross for extraordinary heroism in action connected with the re duction and capture of Tulagi GuvutuTamambogo in the Solo mon Islands area on 15 Sept 1942 The Legion of Merit was awarded him for exceptionally meritorious service as Assistant Operations Officer"
